<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The other is an essentially technological, lis=
t-keeping model: Bank deposits are money, and the job of banks is to keep t=
rack of who has money, and move it around when one person wants to send mon=
ey to another person.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Both of these functions are, of course, true a=
nd important. You could separate them conceptually: You could have one sort=
 of company be in charge of keeping track of everyone=E2=80=99s money and d=
oing payments, and a different sort of company be in charge of borrowing sh=
ort-term to lend long-term, and of course there are examples of both. But i=
n much of the world, for practical and also historical reasons,=C2=A0those =
functions are combined in banks. And my=C2=A0sense<em>=C2=A0</em>is that mo=
st=C2=A0<em>bankers </em>are mostly=C2=A0<em>finance=C2=A0</em>people, that=
 they think mostly about borrowing short and lending long and the financial=
 risks (credit, liquidity, interest rates) of that model. My sense is that =
most bankers do not come from the list-making world, that what gets them ex=
cited is not improving their list-keeping and number-moving technology.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And so the list-keeping technology of banks is=
=C2=A0not<em>=C2=A0</em>always on the cutting edge. Sometimes financial tec=
hnology upstarts <em>do=C2=A0</em>have good ideas for improving payments me=
chanisms, because traditional bankers simply do not=C2=A0<em>care=C2=A0</em=
>enough about improving payments, because the technological aspects of thei=
r jobs are not what excite traditional bankers. And so you have fintech com=
panies building better payments interfaces than the banks do. You have the =
US banking system=E2=80=99s slow move to real-time electronic payments, wit=
h the Federal Reserve=E2=80=99s=C2=A0FedNow instant payments=C2=A0system <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32188809.258411/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuZnJic2VydmljZXMub3JnL25ld3MvcHJlc3MtcmVsZWFzZXMvMDcyMDIzLWZlZG5=
vdy1saXZlLWFubm91bmNlbWVudA/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcdff068d" itemprop=3D"=
StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #00000=
0; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-botto=
m-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> rol=
ling out last week</a> to =E2=80=9C35=C2=A0early-adopting banks and credit =
unions.=E2=80=9D And of course you have crypto, which is <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32188809.258411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS9mZWF0dXJlcy8yMDIyLXRoZS1jcnlwdG8tc3RvcnkvP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA3MjU=
yM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV=
90ZXJtPTIzMDcyNSZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6=
a3df9da" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" s=
tyle=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wid=
th: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgrou=
nd-color: #ccc;"> in large part</a> about building a system for keeping tra=
ck of money that aims to be an improvement over=C2=A0banks. And you have pr=
oposals for <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/321888=
09.258411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZmVkZXJhbHJlc2VydmUuZ292L2NlbnRyYWwtYmFuay1kaWdpd=
GFsLWN1cnJlbmN5Lmh0bQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd4bd4804" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> central b=
ank digital currencies</a>, which would take some ideas from crypto and use=
 them to build a system for keeping track of the money without involving ba=
nks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You could imagine the world going a different =
way. If you started from scratch in 2023, you might say =E2=80=9Cwe should =
have a large=C2=A0well-run=C2=A0<em>tech=C2=A0</em>company that is in charg=
e of keeping the databases of the money and moving numbers around in those =
databases, because that is what tech companies do, and then finance people =
could build all the borrowing-short-to-lend-long infrastructure on top of t=
hat.=E2=80=9D Maybe the list-keeping tech company would also do the financi=
al stuff, because its control of the lists and the payments would be an adv=
antage in funding and lending, or maybe it would build open platforms and o=
ther, more specialized companies would do the funding and the lending. (Aga=
in, these questions are relevant to many crypto=C2=A0platforms.) And of cou=
rse you would have to build a regulatory system to make all of this work fa=
irly and robustly.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But in the actual world <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32188809.258411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuZnQuY29t=
L2NvbnRlbnQvYmIyNDZmNDEtNGU2Ny00MWM1LWFlMDUtN2JmMWZhZTQ1ZjY3/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB2bdc0453" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> here=E2=80=99s a funny Financial Times story=
 about</a> how Deutsche Bank AG bought Postbank, another German bank, in 20=
10 and then spent 13 years trying to figure out how to combine Postbank=E2=
=80=99s list of account holders with Deutsche Bank=E2=80=99s=C2=A0list of a=
ccount holders:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Inside one of the lender=E2=80=99s buildings i=
n Frankfurt, a 200-strong team of retail bankers and IT specialists were ra=
cing to complete the final 2,833 tasks needed to transfer the remaining dat=
a of German lender Postbank=E2=80=99s 12mn customers over to Deutsche=E2=80=
=99s computer systems.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As the meticulous plan, rehearsed several time=
s in previous months, unfolded, an unsuspecting member of the team opened a=
 dishwasher in mid-cycle, with the escaping steam setting off a smoke detec=
tor and forcing the evacuation of the building. Precious minutes were squan=
dered before firefighters gave the all-clear.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The final 2,833 tasks! And:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The groundwork was laid just as the coronaviru=
s pandemic struck Europe in the spring of 2020, when for the next 18 months=
 more than 1,000 staff analysed the Postbank data, worked out how to move i=
t and unearthed complications.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One stemmed from the fact that some Postbank c=
lients were erroneously still listed as residents of defunct states such as=
 Czechoslovakia or Yugoslavia, designations that Deutsche=E2=80=99s systems=
 rejected. =E2=80=9CIn such a project, you not only have to deal with decad=
es of data and history but also with junk data,=E2=80=9D said Karsten Roesc=
h, who ran the Unity project alongside Peschke.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I assume that there are people who work at, li=
ke, Stripe, who are <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/clic=
k/32188809.258411/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cua2FsenVtZXVzLmNvbS8yMDEwLzA2LzE3L2ZhbHNla=
G9vZHMtcHJvZ3JhbW1lcnMtYmVsaWV2ZS1hYm91dC1uYW1lcy8/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23c=
B7815df58" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank"=
 style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-w=
idth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgr=
ound-color: #ccc;">rolling their eyes</a> so hard at this that they have in=
jured themselves. Not in a =E2=80=9Ccombining two lists of bank accounts is=
 trivial=E2=80=9D way, but in a =E2=80=9Cwell yes obviously you have to dea=
l with defunct address data but why don=E2=80=99t you have people who are t=
hinking about that=E2=80=9D way. =E2=80=9CWe are a tech company,=E2=80=9D s=
ome bankers are fond of saying, but not=C2=A0<em>really.</em></p>
