<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The FDIC observed that some insure=
d depository institutions (IDIs) are not reporting estimated uninsured depo=
sits in accordance with the instructions to the Consolidated Reports of Con=
dition and Income (Call Report). For example, some institutions incorrectly=
 reduced the amount reported to the extent that the uninsured deposits are =
collateralized by pledged assets; this is incorrect because in and of itsel=
f, the existence of collateral has no bearing on the portion of a deposit t=
hat is covered by federal deposit insurance. Additionally, some institution=
s incorrectly reduced the amount reported on Schedule RC-O by excluding int=
ercompany deposit balances of subsidiaries.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You might naively think that if you asked one =
of the largest banks in the US =E2=80=9Chow much money do you have from dep=
ositors with more than $250,000 at your bank,=E2=80=9D it could spend, you =
know, a few hours looking at the data and get back to you with an answer th=
at was accurate to within 10%. But you=E2=80=99d be wrong!</p>
